Define the `cocardinal` and `cocountable` filters as those consisting of sets whose complements have a given cardinality/ are countable.

**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion ∀ᶠ x in cocardinal hreg, p x) ↔ #{ x | ¬p x } < c := Iff.rfl ```

Let's make the connection to `Filter.cofinite`:
```suggestion

@[simp] lemma cocardinal_aleph0_eq_cofinite :
    cocardinal α isRegular_aleph0 = cofinite := by
  aesop

```
I think you'll need to add `import Mathlib.Order.Filter.Cofinite` up top to make this work.

```suggestion

variable (α) in
```
I've resolved all other comments, but can you comment on why you would like to do this? This would mean that you need to make the dependence on α explicit much more often, right?

I suggested this because otherwise the expression `cocardinal hreg` contains no information from which we can deduce `α`. Indeed if you test the following:
```lean
variable (hreg : c.IsRegular)
#check cocardinal hreg
```
you will see that the output is `cocardinal hreg : Filter ?m.990` indicating that `α` is a metavariable.

So I think you should make this change.

```suggestion
variable {c : Cardinal.{u}} {hreg : c.IsRegular}
```
and throughout below

```suggestion
def cocardinal (hreg : c.IsRegular) : Filter α := by
  apply ofCardinalUnion {s | Cardinal.mk s < c} (lt_of_lt_of_le (nat_lt_aleph0 2) hreg.aleph0_le)
  · refine fun s hS hSc ↦ lt_of_le_of_lt (mk_sUnion_le _) <| mul_lt_of_lt hreg.aleph0_le hS ?_
    exact iSup_lt_of_isRegular hreg hS fun i ↦ hSc i i.property
  · exact fun _ hSc _ ht ↦ lt_of_le_of_lt (mk_le_mk_of_subset ht) hSc
```

```suggestion
instance instCardinalInterFilter_cocardinal : CardinalInterFilter (cocardinal α hreg) c where
  cardinal_sInter_mem S hS hSs := by
    rw [mem_cocardinal, Set.compl_sInter]
    apply lt_of_le_of_lt (mk_sUnion_le _)
    apply mul_lt_of_lt hreg.aleph0_le (lt_of_le_of_lt mk_image_le hS)
    apply iSup_lt_of_isRegular hreg <| lt_of_le_of_lt mk_image_le hS
    intro i
    aesop
```

It's better to avoid line breaking within a term if possible. Also, this is a job for set-builder notation:
```suggestion
theorem hasBasis_cocardinal :
    HasBasis (cocardinal hreg) {s : Set α | #s < c} compl :=
```

```suggestion
lemma frequently_cocardinal_mem {s : Set α} :
```

```suggestion
theorem frequently_cocardinal {p : α → Prop} :
    (∃ᶠ x in cocardinal hreg, p x) ↔ c ≤ # { x | p x } := by
  simp only [Filter.Frequently, eventually_cocardinal, not_not,coe_setOf, not_lt]
```

```suggestion
    sᶜ ∈ @cocardinal α c hreg :=
  Set.compl_mem_cocardinal <| lt_of_lt_of_le (Finite.lt_aleph0 hs) (hreg.aleph0_le)
```
(And of course the `@` will disappear when you make `α` explicit.)

```suggestion
  rw [Cardinal.countable_iff_lt_aleph_one, mem_cocardinal]
  
end Filter
```

